
[1]tough

   TOUGH, a. tuf.

   1. Having the quality of flexibility without brittleness; yielding to
   force without breaking. The ligaments of animals and of India rubber
   are remarkably tough. Tough timber, like young ash, is the most proper
   for the shafts and springs of a carriage.

   2. Firm; strong; not easily broken; able to endure hardship; as an
   animal of a tough frame.

   3. Not easily separated; viscous; clammy; tenacious; ropy; as tough
   phlegm.

   4. Stiff; not flexible.
